"a.绷紧的 【英】 adj. 绷紧的 (having no slack；tightly drawn) 【考】 反义词：loose or unfirm(松或不稳的); slack(松的) 【例】 a taut string / Her nerves are rather taut. adj. 绷紧的; 紧张的 【记】读: 套它, 用套索套住它, 再收紧－紧的 【类】slacken: tautness = dilute: strength松弛消除紧张度 = 稀释消除浓度taut: commodious = extraordinary: purlieu紧张的不是宽敞的 = 不寻常的不是常去的地方 【反】loosen unfirm(松的); slack(adj 松弛的) 【记】音：套它，用绳索套住它并拉紧；taught 教，教学，教训→学校里教学都是秩序井然，严肃紧张 taut (adj.)  mid-13c., tohte ""stretched or pulled tight,"" possibly from tog-, past participle stem of Old English teon ""to pull, drag,"" from Proto-Germanic *tugn, from PIE *deuk- ""to lead"" (see duke (n.)), which would connect it to tow (v.) and tie. Related: Tautness."
